subSubSection.paragraph:
Description
: Fore wing length 
15‒17 mm
. Body length 
20‒21 mm
. Antenna with 53‒57 flagellomeres. Head quite narrowed behind eyes, temple in lateral view 0.7 × as long as compound eye in female, 0.8 × in male (
Fig. 16D
). Lateral ocellus touching inner margin of compound eye. Face quite narrow (
Fig. 16B
). occipital carina centrally with a very distinct dorsal notch. Face below antennal sockets shagreened with distinct and very dense punctures. Malar space very narrow, about 0.1 × as long as mandibular base. Mandibular gape obtuse, with internal angles. First flagellomere 3.5 × as long as wide. Central flagellomeres stout, about 1.2 × as long as wide. Mesoscutum polished with very weak punctures. Mesopleuron shagreened with punctures quite dense, centrally with strong wave-like rugulose sculpture (
Fig. 16C
). Epicnemial carina, in antero-ventral view, with pleurosternal angles very distinct, right-angled or slightly acute, slightly anterior to sternal angles. Scutellum with lateral carinae in basal 0.5. Propodeum dorsally polished with weak scarce punctures and the anterior and posterior transverse carina very strongly raised (
Fig. 16E
), laterally with rugulose wave-like sculpture. Anterior transverse carina anteriorly often with two short parallel carinae centrally. Central longitudinal carinae strong, delimiting a slightly elongate area superomedia which often is open posteriorly. Lateral longitudinal carinae weak or missing (
Fig. 16E
). Submetapleural carina strongly raised. Sclerotised part of first sternite ending level to spiracle. Hind trochantellus shorter than wide in dorsal view. Hind femur slender, about 7.0 × as long as wide. Inner spur of hind tibia long, about 0.5 × as long as hind metatarsus. Wing membrane infuscate. Ramellus distinct, reaching about 0.3 × the width of the discosubmarginal cell. Radius weakly sinuous. Nervellus broken below the middle by the discoidella.
